snippet.textDisplay:
Ark is one of the worst games i've ever played in 30 years. It's so horribly inconsiderate of your time. Every single thing you do is so obnoxiously and pointlessly tedious and time consuming. And the the risk vs reward is insanely imbalanced. The punishment for small screw ups far outweighs the reward. And many times you are severely punished for no reason at all just because of outrageous rng spawns or just glitches. Ark is the definition of bad gameplay design. It's laughable that they would rather keep adding content instead of fix what's already there.

I know you're a small indie group but you really need to go play some Capcom or Nintendo games and learn how to make a proper game. Or hell even Minecraft. You feed a dog a few bones and he's yours. Spending 4 real life hours taming a virtual animal in a video game is pathetic design. Miyamoto would be baffled at your game for being so anti-player.
